  "prompt": "How do people count in Denmark?",
  "response": "In Denmark, counting is done using the Danish numeral system, which is similar to other Germanic languages. Here\u2019s how to count from 1 to 10 in Danish:\n\n1. En  \n2. To  \n3. Tre  \n4. Fire  \n5. Fem  \n6. Seks  \n7. Syv  \n8. Otte  \n9. Ni  \n10. Ti  \n\nDanish numbers are relatively straightforward for small quantities, but the system becomes more complex for larger numbers. For example, the word for 50 is \"halvtreds,\" which is derived from an old counting system based on 20s. If you\u2019re learning Danish, numbers can take some practice to master!\n\nLet me know if you'd like to explore more about counting in Danish or other aspects of the language!",
